Paris Saint-Germain are said to have briefly discussed sending Ander Herrera to Tottenham as part of a potential swap deal for Tanguy Ndombele, according to reports. Club-to-club discussions remain ongoing between the two sides after conversations began late last week over a move that could see the 25-year-old reunite with old manager Mauricio Pochettino. Tottenham are keen to move Ndombele on now that it’s clear he seems unlikely to fulfil his potential in north London. That’s despite so many moments of huge promise during a rollercoaster two-and-a-half seasons at Spurs following his club-record £55million transfer from Lyon in 2019. Full Details Of Contract Pique Signed Under Bartomeu Has Been… Andy Carroll’s  Big-Money Move To Liverpool In 2011 Voted… Nonetheless, technical director Fabio Paratici believes Ndombele’s departure could help free up some additional funds to spend this month. PSG have already reportedly offered Leandro Paredes in part-exchange for Ndombele but Tottenham were not interested in the Argentine. Now The Athletic (08:58 of podcast) claim former Manchester United midfielder Ander Herrera has also been suggested as potential makeweight in a deal. The Spaniard is believed to be happy at PSG though and would only want to return to England to play for Manchester United. Roma are also believed to have held talks over a swap deal for Ndombele. POLL It’s been claimed in Italy that former Aston Villa midfielder Jordan Veretout could head the other way to Spurs.